
Simple script to break down the number of files changed, lines added and lines deleted by week in a given Git repository. The file and line information is based on the Git diff output and is reaped from the `git log` command.

============
 Usage
============

  Usage: git-historian [options]
      -r, --repository REPOSITORY      Location of the local git repository
                                         (default: current directory)
      -f, --format FORMAT              Output format
                                       (options: csv, normal. default: normal)
  